<ol><li>Consider a ball P in&nbsp;<b>uniform circular motion</b>, the coordinates of P are&nbsp;\(x=r\cos\theta\)&nbsp;and&nbsp;\(y=r\sin\theta\)&nbsp;where&nbsp;\(\theta\)&nbsp;is the angle between the x-axis and the radial line OP.</li><li>Consider the <b>shadow of the ball</b>&nbsp;and the shadow of a&nbsp;<b>pendulum</b>, the two shadows <b>match each other exactly&nbsp;</b>when their time periods are matched.</li><li>So at any instance they have the&nbsp;<b>same horizontal motion</b>&nbsp;so their acceleration are the same.</li><li>The&nbsp;<b>component of acceleration</b>&nbsp;of the ball parallel to the screen is.&nbsp;\[a=-\omega^2r\cos\theta=-\omega^2x\]</li><li>So the acceleration of the bob is also&nbsp;\(a=-\omega^2x\).</li></ol>